HEADWORD: Intercision
<hw>In`ter*ci"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intercisio</ets> a cutting through, fr. <ets>intercidere</ets> to
cut asunder.]</ety> <def>A cutting off, through, or asunder;
interruption.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

